\subsection{Phonon calculation}

Phonons are calculated using the finite difference method, in which we considered 16 atoms around the rotating bond that are mostly affected by the C--C bond rotation as highlighted in Fig.~\ref{fig:phonon}. All the transition states have been confirmed via one-and-only-one imaginary frequency, which indicate that these are indeed first-order transition states. These phonons are used to calculate the zero point energy correction to the formation energy and kinetic activation barrier.  The prefactor to the reaction rate within the harmonic transition state theory has been also calculated using these phonons:  $\nu = \Pi_i^{3N} \nu_i^{\rm P}/\Pi_i^{(3N-1)} \nu_i^{\rm TS}$, where $\nu_i^{\rm P} (\nu_i^{\rm TS})$ are the normal mode frequencies corresponding to pristine (transition state) structure. 


